# Commit Message Guidelines
#
# 1. Technical description only (no branding)
# 2. Use imperative mood: Fix bug not Fixed bug
# 3. First line: 50-72 characters max
# 4. Body: Explain what and why (not how)
#
# Example:
# FIX: Prevent buffer overflow in DHT message handling
#
# Validate message size before processing to prevent DoS attacks.
# Ensures payloads don't exceed 64KB limit.
# Related to issue #123

